# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#Subtopic Canvas_Layer

Canvas_Layer allocates a temporary offscreen Bitmap to draw into. When the drawing is complete,
the Bitmap is drawn into the Canvas. 

Canvas_Layer is saved in a stack along with other saved state. When state with a Canvas_Layer
is restored, the offscreen Bitmap is drawn into the previous layer.

Canvas_Layer may be initialized with the contents of the previous layer. When Canvas_Layer is
restored, its Bitmap can be modified by Paint passed to Canvas_Layer to apply Color_Alpha,
Color_Filter, Image_Filter, and Blend_Mode.

#Method int saveLayer(const SkRect* bounds, const SkPaint* paint)

Saves Canvas_Matrix, Canvas_Clip, and Draw_Filter (Draw_Filter deprecated on most platforms),
and allocates an offscreen Bitmap for subsequent drawing.
Calling restore() discards changes to Canvas_Matrix, Canvas_Clip, and Draw_Filter,
and draws the offscreen bitmap.
The Canvas_Matrix, Canvas_Clip, and Draw_Filter are restored to their state when save() was called. 

Canvas_Matrix may be changed by translate(), scale(), rotate(), skew(), concat(), setMatrix, and resetMatrix.
Canvas_Clip may be changed by clipRect, clipRRect, clipPath, clipRegion.
Draw_Filter may be changed by setDrawFilter.

Rect bounds suggests but does not define the offscreen size. To clip drawing to a specific rectangle,
use clipRect.

Optional Paint paint applies Color_Alpha, Color_Filter, Image_Filter, and Blend_Mode when restore() is called.

Call restoreToCount with result to restore this and subsequent saves.

#Param bounds  Used as a hint to limit the size of the offscreen; may be nullptr. ##
#Param paint  Used when restore() is called to draw the offscreen; may be nullptr. ##

#Return  Depth of saved stack. ##

#Example
void draw(SkCanvas* canvas) {
    SkPaint paint, blur;
    blur.setImageFilter(SkImageFilter::MakeBlur(3, 3, nullptr));
    canvas->saveLayer(nullptr, &blur);
    SkRect rect = { 25, 25, 50, 50};
    canvas->drawRect(rect, paint);
    canvas->translate(50, 50);
    paint.setColor(SK_ColorRED);
    canvas->drawRect(rect, paint);
    canvas->restore();
}
##

#ToDo incomplete ##

##

#Method int saveLayer(const SkRect& bounds, const SkPaint* paint) 

Saves Canvas_Matrix, Canvas_Clip, and Draw_Filter (Draw_Filter deprecated on most platforms),
and allocates an offscreen Bitmap for subsequent drawing.
Calling restore() discards changes to Canvas_Matrix, Canvas_Clip, and Draw_Filter,
and draws the offscreen Bitmap.
The Canvas_Matrix, Canvas_Clip, and Draw_Filter are restored to their state when save() was called. 

Canvas_Matrix may be changed by translate(), scale(), rotate(), skew(), concat(), setMatrix, and resetMatrix.
Canvas_Clip may be changed by clipRect, clipRRect, clipPath, clipRegion.
Draw_Filter may be changed by setDrawFilter.

bounds suggests but does not define the offscreen size. To clip drawing to a specific rectangle,
use clipRect.

Optional Paint paint applies Color_Alpha, Color_Filter, Image_Filter, and Blend_Mode when restore() is called.

Call restoreToCount with result to restore this and subsequent saves.

#Param bounds  Used as a hint to limit the size of the offscreen; may be nullptr. ##
#Param paint  Used when restore() is called to draw the offscreen; may be nullptr. ##

#Return  Depth of saved stack. ##

#Example
void draw(SkCanvas* canvas) {
    SkPaint paint, blur;
    blur.setImageFilter(SkImageFilter::MakeBlur(3, 3, nullptr));
    canvas->saveLayer(SkRect::MakeWH(90, 90), &blur);
    SkRect rect = { 25, 25, 50, 50};
    canvas->drawRect(rect, paint);
    canvas->translate(50, 50);
    paint.setColor(SK_ColorRED);
    canvas->drawRect(rect, paint);
    canvas->restore();
}
