# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#Topic Canvas_Clip

Canvas_Clip is built from a stack of clipping paths. Each Path in the
stack can be constructed from one or more Path_Contour elements. The 
Path_Contour may be composed of any number of Path_Verb segments. Each
Path_Contour forms a closed area; Path_Fill_Type defines the area enclosed
by Path_Contour.

Canvas_Clip stack of Path elements successfully restrict the Path area. Each
Path is transformed by Canvas_Matrix, then intersected with or subtracted from the 
prior Canvas_Clip to form the replacement Canvas_Clip. Use SkClipOp_kDifference
to subtract Path from Canvas_Clip; use SkClipOp_kIntersect to intersect Path
with Canvas_Clip.

A clipping Path may be anti-aliased; if Path, after transformation, is
composed of horizontal and vertical lines, clearing Anti-alias allows whole pixels
to either be inside or outside the clip. The fastest drawing has a aliased,
rectanglar clip.

If clipping Path has Anti-alias set, clip may partially clip a pixel, requiring
that drawing blend partially with the destination along the edge. A rotated 
rectangular anti-aliased clip looks smoother but draws slower.

Canvas_Clip can combine with Rect and Round_Rect primitives; like
Path, these are transformed by Canvas_Matrix before they are combined with Canvas_Clip.

Canvas_Clip can combine with Region. Region is assumed to be in Device coordinates
and is unaffected by Canvas_Matrix.

#Example
    #Description
        Draw a red circle with an aliased clip and an anti-aliased clip.
        Use an image filter to zoom into the pixels drawn.
        The edge of the aliased clip fully draws pixels in the red circle.
        The edge of the anti-aliased clip partially draws pixels in the red circle.
    ##
    canvas->clear(SK_ColorWHITE);
    SkPaint redPaint, scalePaint;
    redPaint.setAntiAlias(true);
    redPaint.setColor(SK_ColorRED);
    canvas->save();
    for (bool antialias : { false, true } ) {
        canvas->save();
        canvas->clipRect(SkRect::MakeWH(19.5f, 21.5f), antialias);
        canvas->drawCircle(17, 21, 8, redPaint);
        canvas->restore();
        canvas->translate(16, 0);
    }
    canvas->restore();
    SkMatrix matrix;
    matrix.setScale(6, 6);
    scalePaint.setImageFilter(
            SkImageFilter::MakeMatrixFilter(matrix, kNone_SkFilterQuality, nullptr));
    SkCanvas::SaveLayerRec saveLayerRec(
            nullptr, &scalePaint, SkCanvas::kInitWithPrevious_SaveLayerFlag); 
    canvas->saveLayer(saveLayerRec);
    canvas->restore();
##

#Method void clipRect(const SkRect& rect, SkClipOp, bool doAntiAlias)

Replace Canvas_Clip with the intersection or difference of Canvas_Clip and rect,
with an aliased or anti-aliased clip edge. rect is transformed by Canvas_Matrix
before it is combined with Canvas_Clip.

#Param  rect  Rectangle to combine with Canvas_Clip. ##
#Param  op    Clip_Op to apply to Canvas_Clip. ##
#Param  doAntiAlias  true if Canvas_Clip is to be anti-aliased. ##

#Example
void draw(SkCanvas* canvas) {
    canvas->clear(SK_ColorWHITE);
    canvas->rotate(10);
    SkPaint paint;
    paint.setAntiAlias(true);
    for (auto alias: { false, true } ) {
        canvas->save();
        canvas->clipRect(SkRect::MakeWH(90, 120), SkClipOp::kIntersect, alias);
        canvas->drawCircle(100, 100, 60, paint);
        canvas->restore();
        canvas->translate(80, 0);
    }
}
##

#ToDo incomplete ##

##

#Method void clipRect(const SkRect& rect, SkClipOp op) 

Replace Canvas_Clip with the intersection or difference of Canvas_Clip and rect.
Resulting Canvas_Clip is aliased; pixels are fully contained by the clip.
rect is transformed by Canvas_Matrix
before it is combined with Canvas_Clip.

#Param  rect  Rectangle to combine with Canvas_Clip. ##
#Param  op    Clip_Op to apply to Canvas_Clip. ##

#Example
void draw(SkCanvas* canvas) {
    canvas->clear(SK_ColorWHITE);
    SkPaint paint;
    for (SkClipOp op: { SkClipOp::kIntersect, SkClipOp::kDifference } ) {
        canvas->save();
        canvas->clipRect(SkRect::MakeWH(90, 120), op, false);
        canvas->drawCircle(100, 100, 60, paint);
        canvas->restore();
        canvas->translate(80, 0);
    }
}
##

#ToDo incomplete ##

##

#Method void clipRect(const SkRect& rect, bool doAntiAlias = false) 

Replace Canvas_Clip with the intersection of Canvas_Clip and rect.
Resulting Canvas_Clip is aliased; pixels are fully contained by the clip.
rect is transformed by Canvas_Matrix
before it is combined with Canvas_Clip.

#Param  rect  Rectangle to combine with Canvas_Clip. ##
#Param  doAntiAlias  true if Canvas_Clip is to be anti-aliased. ##

#Example
    #Description
        A circle drawn in pieces looks uniform when drawn aliased.
        The same circle pieces blend with pixels more than once when anti-aliased,
        visible as a thin pair of lines through the right circle.
    ##
void draw(SkCanvas* canvas) {
    canvas->clear(SK_ColorWHITE);
    SkPaint paint;
    paint.setAntiAlias(true);
    paint.setColor(0x8055aaff);
    SkRect clipRect = { 0, 0, 90.4f, 120.4f };
    for (auto alias: { false, true } ) {
        canvas->save();
        canvas->clipRect(clipRect, SkClipOp::kIntersect, alias);
        canvas->drawCircle(70, 100, 60, paint);
        canvas->restore();
        canvas->save();
        canvas->clipRect(clipRect, SkClipOp::kDifference, alias);
        canvas->drawCircle(70, 100, 60, paint);
        canvas->restore();
        canvas->translate(120, 0);
    }
}
